This is a great recipe, but unfortunately what gets missed by many is the "coarse" salt. 1/4 cup of coarse salt is a WHOLE lot less than 1/4 cup of table salt. Make sure you're using the right stuff. If you don't have coarse or kosher or sea salt, just add it tablespoon at a time until it tastes salty, but not overbearing. This is just a brine, people!

