Rating: 4
Succulent and delicious, these come out delectable every time. I'm not a big pork fan myself, but my family is, and even I adored this recipe along with the rest of the gang. I would respectfully disagree with an earlier cook's suggestion to try this recipe with lamb instead of pork. Brines work best with meats like pork, chicken and turkey, not beef and lamb. Brining can leach away the juices from beef and lamb and take away, rather than enhance, their tenderness and flavor. There's a chemical reason for this which is beyond my ability to explain, but I would suggest brining as a successful, fool-proof technique best used with pork and poultry only.

