Rating: 4
For those who found the meat too salty and who used kosher salt, they might have been using Morton brand kosher salt, which has a finer flake than Diamond Crystal brand. For THIS PORK CHOP recipe, use 1/4 cup Diamond Crystal kosher salt OR 3 tablespoons Morton kosher salt OR 2 tablespoons table salt. The general conversion is 1/2 cup Diamond Crystal kosher salt OR 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons Morton kosher salt OR 1/4 cup table salt. Hope this clarifies things.

