Cook on 8/28 is right; trichinosis and most bacteria is killed in pork by about 140*...there is no need to cook to "leather" overkill; 150-155* or so is plenty. Pork can be JUST done (medium-well), still juicy and tender and NOT give you diseases. Check Julia Child's recommendation it is the same temp or less than this. Overcooked pork is usually due to killing it to a temp of 170-180*. If you are fearful, cook to 155 and let it rest to come to 160.

