These were delicious. Very moist. But I couldn't taste much of the garlic, and considering the amount on there, that was surprising. It's very important to use the coarse (or Kosher) salt called for here, both in the brine and in the rub-- otherwise the chops will be unbearably salty. As well, patting the chops COMPLETELY dry is crucial to the spice rub adhering properly to the meat. I served the pork with the potato and pea salad from the same issue. Both recipes will be repeated many times over.

