Rating: 3
Liked this dish for the relatively unusual flavor. Kinda B-B-Qish, but not not quite. I started with nice, thick, center-cut pork chops. Skipped the ice (didn't see the need), used dark molassas(all I had) and cut back a little on the salt(which I recommend). Marinaded 10 hours (while at work), and then again cut back a little on the salt in the rub (which I recommend). Grilled on gas Weber 8 mins. per side then let rest for 8 mins. Perfect (which, for me, is slightly pink at bone). Not salty at all. Moist and flavorfull. Previous reviewer makes an excellent point -- the recipe calls for COARSE (or kosher) salt which has much less salt per volume. If using regular salt (which you shouldn't do) you'll have to cut the amount back by probably half.

