Rating: 4
Ths is but a variation of the brining and rub recipes found in "The Complete Meat Cookbook" by Aidells and Kelly (an excellent book, by the way). The amounts of salt and liquid are correct. Be certain you use coarse salt; if using table salt, reduce amount by half. If using thinner cuts, shorten brining time, and don't overcook, or the meat will be tough (especially the leaner cuts). Rinse quickly and dry before grilling. This is an excellent way to prepare pork.

